Let $\tau^n = a_n + \lfloor \tau^n \rceil, a_n \in [0, \frac{1}{2})$</think>
\begin{align*}
\sum_{n = 0}^\infty \frac{\lfloor \tau^n \rceil}{2^n}
&= \sum_{n = 0}^\infty \frac{a_n + \lfloor \tau^n \rceil - a_n}{2^n}\\
&= \sum_{n = 0}^\infty \left(\frac{\lfloor \tau^n \rceil}{2^n} - \frac{a_n}{2^n}\right)\\
&= \sum_{n = 0}^\infty \frac{\lfloor \tau^n \rceil}{2^n} - \sum_{n = 0}^\infty \frac{a_n}{2^n}\\
&= \sum_{n = 0}^\infty \frac{\lfloor \tau^n \rceil}{2^n} - F_\tau
\end{align*}
where $F_\tau$ is the sum of the fractional part of $\left(\frac{1 + \sqrt{5}}{2}\right)^n,$ which is
\begin{align*}
\sum_{n = 0}^\infty \left(\frac{1 + \sqrt{5}}{2}\right)^n \sum_{k = 0}^\infty \left(\frac{1 + \sqrt{5}}{2}\right)^{-(k+1)} &= \sum_{n = 0}^\infty \left(\frac{1 + \sqrt{5}}{2}\right)^n \frac{2}{-3 + \sqrt{5}}\\
&= \frac{14 + 8\sqrt{5}}{22}(2 - \sqrt{5})\\
&= -4
\end{align*}
so $F_\tau = -4.$  Therefore
\[\sum_{n = 0}^\infty \frac{\lfloor \tau^n \rceil}{2^n} = \boxed{4}.\] <answer>4</answer>

